heaviest_rainfall.status: Today's storm ranked 7th for total rainfall with 23.86mm having fallen, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  8.3mm per hour fell at points during the storm which lasted 31.0 hours.  The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 09 November 2025, with precipitation totalling 47.89mm.  The rain fell at 24.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 27.6mm per hour was the peak rain rate recorded today ranking 2nd in our overall records.  The storm lasted 2.6 hours and 6.1mm of rain fell.  On 02 September 2025, the rain fell at an exceptional rate, peaking at 34.3mm per hour, the heaviest downpour recorded.  A total of 21.19mm fell over the 15.0 hour storm.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 31.0 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 7th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 23.86mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  The record duration for continuous rain was set on 09 November 2025, the storm lasted 144.8 hours with a total precipitation of 47.89mm and it reached 24.6mm per hour at times.
